WILLIAMS Troost-Ekong’s target now is to go one better than the previous AFCON tournament where the Super Eagles just missed out to Algeria in the final four, and the defender believes it’s possible with the adoring support of the Nigeria faithful.   Mhango brace earns Malawi important win over Zimbabwe     Nigeria v Sudan: Eguavoen sticks to Iheanacho, Awoniyi…     How Nigeria High Commission spurs Super Eagles to victory   “For me, leaving Watford at the time in the difficult situation that we are in, I didn’t want to leave without making this a meaningful tournament,” Troost-Ekong said. He continued:  “I’ve set my sights on trying to go all the way. Last AFCON we got to the semi-finals and only missed out in the last minute. This time we want to do better, I don’t want to waste my time here because I would want to help Watford. I want to go and win because at least when I get back home, I have something to show for it. That’s my objective.